<figureCitation id="1375F6C0FFC09E1E831721BB3BC649D1" box="[605,694,158,184]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[341,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[340,1247,190,1712]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 3. Species of Gentianaceae from the Parque Municipal de Mucugê - Projeto Sempre Viva (PMM), Bahia, Brazil: Calolisianthus pedunculatus (A), Chelonanthus purpurascens (B), Curtia verticillaris (C), Curtia tenuifolia (D), Prepusa montana (E), Schultesia bahiensis (F), Schultesia crenuliflora (G), Schultesia pachyphylla (H). Scale bars:A: 2 cm; B: 1 cm; C: 0,5 cm; D: 0,5 cm; E: 2 cm; F–H: 1 cm. Photo A, B, E, F, G and H by Maria Luiza Silveira de Carvalho; C and D by Vinicius Dittrich and Gustavo Shimizu, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424491/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF1EA45FFC09E1E81C221C33DD148DD" blockId="12.[136,1452,230,869]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E81C221C339BC4869" box="[136,204,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Herbs</emphasis>
, ca. 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E804821C338374869" box="[258,327,230,256]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="40.0">40 cm</quantity>
tall. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E80CA21C3389A4869" box="[384,490,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Branches</emphasis>
green, cylindrical, costate. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E825521C23A1D4869" box="[799,877,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Leaves</emphasis>
opposite, sessile, discolorous, blades 1.2 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E841221C33CD74869" box="[1368,1447,230,256]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="0.2">0.2 cm</quantity>
, linear, membranaceous, glabrous, attenuate at base, acute at apex, entire at margin. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E8567202F3DB3484D" box="[1069,1219,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Inflorescence</emphasis>
in terminal biparous cyme, 4-flowered, sessile. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E80F8200B3B7E4821" box="[434,526,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Flowers</emphasis>
heterostylous, 5-merous, pedicel ca. 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E82E5200B3A994821" box="[943,1001,302,328]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
; calyx 0.3 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E8533200B3DB74821" box="[1145,1223,302,328]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="0.2">0.2 cm</quantity>
, green to vinaceous, keeled, not winged, tubular, glabrous; corolla yellowish, pink or purple, infundibuliform, tube 4.3 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E85BF20773C494805" box="[1269,1337,338,364]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
, lobes 3.6 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E81EA2053398948F9" box="[160,249,374,400]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="6.6">6.6 mm</quantity>
, base elliptic to obovate, apex acute; stamens 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E824E20533A2D48F9" box="[772,861,374,400]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.7 mm</quantity>
, isodynamous, adnate, conation 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E858720533C3E48F9" box="[1229,1358,374,400]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="0.9" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.7">0.7–1.1 cm</quantity>
, anthers basifixed; ovary 1–1.2 × 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E80EB20BF3B5148DD" box="[417,545,410,436]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.6 cm</quantity>
, style ca. 
<quantity id="4CB647A0FFC09E1E83C520BF3BB948DD" box="[655,713,410,436]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
, stigma bilobed. 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E82C220BE3AB248DD" box="[904,962,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Fruit</emphasis>
septifragal capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354B9CEFFC09E1E81F720983BFE4BE5" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF1EA45FFC09E1E81F720983BFE4BE5" blockId="12.[136,1452,230,869]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E81F7209838AE48BE" bold="true" box="[189,478,445,472]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Habitat and distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E91C6FFC09E1E834B209B3BCB48B1" authorityName="Knoblauch" authorityYear="1894" box="[513,699,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Curtia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E834B209B3BCB48B1" box="[513,699,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Curtia tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed throughout the American continent, with the exception of North America, having been collected in areas of “campo limpo”, “campo rupestre”, Cerrado and “Amazonian savanna” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E81B723233BE14B49" author="Crespo, S. R. M. &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira, W." box="[253,657,518,544]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="423 - 444" refId="ref13891" refString="Crespo, S. R. M. &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira, W. (2009) Revisao taxonomica do genero Curtia (Gentianaceae). Rodriguesia 60: 423 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860200960214" type="journal article" year="2009">Crespo &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E83D123233A094B49" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[667,889,518,544]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E83B523223A474B49" box="[767,823,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E82C923233D044B49" author="Bissoli, V. F. &amp; Calio, M. F." box="[899,1140,518,544]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" refId="ref12583" refString="Bissoli, V. F. &amp; Calio, M. F. (2020) Curtia in Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Avilable from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 7757 (accessed 30 November 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bissoli &amp; Calió 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F359AAD5FFC09E1E85EE23233D9B4B49" box="[1188,1259,518,544]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it has confirmed occurrences for the states of 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E8088230F388B4B2D" box="[450,507,554,580]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Acre</collectingRegion>
, Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E83CC230F3BAA4B2D" box="[646,730,554,580]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Amapá</collectingRegion>
, Pará, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E8268230F3AF54B2D" box="[802,901,554,580]" country="Brazil" name="Roraima" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Roraima</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E82C5230F3AA34B2D" box="[911,979,554,580]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E8294230F3D224B2D" box="[990,1106,554,580]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E8516230F3D9B4B2D" box="[1116,1259,554,580]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E85BF230F3CD74B2D" box="[1269,1447,554,580]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Distrito Federal</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E81C2236B39BC4B01" box="[136,204,590,616]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E8193236B38B14B01" box="[217,449,590,616]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E8084236B3B144B01" box="[462,612,590,616]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E833B236B3A7B4B01" box="[625,779,590,616]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E8252236B3AFE4B01" box="[792,910,590,616]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E82D0236B3A994B01" box="[922,1001,590,616]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498A24A7FFC09E1E82BC236B3DBC4B01" box="[1014,1228,590,616]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
and 
