<subSubSection id="C354B9CEFFC09E1E81F723B03D0F4A0D" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF1EA45FFC09E1E81F723B038044A75" blockId="12.[136,1452,230,869]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E81F723B0384E4BC6" bold="true" box="[189,318,661,687]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">Comments</emphasis>
:—This is the only species of the genus that presents heterostyly, its flowers being tristylous. In addition, the variation in color and flower size justify the several synonyms of this species (Crespo &amp; Marcondes- Ferreira 2009, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E806623FB3B7A4B91" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[300,522,734,760]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E80DA23FA38B74B91" box="[400,455,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Found with flowers and fruits all year round (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E855E23FB3CD74B91" author="Crespo, S. R. M. &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira, W." box="[1044,1447,734,760]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="423 - 444" refId="ref13891" refString="Crespo, S. R. M. &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira, W. (2009) Revisao taxonomica do genero Curtia (Gentianaceae). Rodriguesia 60: 423 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860200960214" type="journal article" year="2009">Crespo &amp; Marcondes-Ferreira 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF97B4FFC09E1E81C2222738184A75" author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[136,360,770,796]" pageId="12" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis id="B93A3657FFC09E1E81A6222638554A75" box="[236,293,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
